script.name: Lib.Cmd.Trade.GetStationBestPrice
script.description: Lib Gen: Returns closest station with best price

line.comment: * Min amount recently added. For Buy, it'll keep searching until it find a station with the min amount. null if none found
* For sell, needs to have enough free volume for ware to be returned. and same as with buy, null if none found
* do if $loops > 2
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: security check', $Station, null, null, null, null
* No idea why I used storage percentage here
* $Storage = $Station-> get ware storage percentage: ware=$Ware
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: none in stock', $Station, null, null, null, null
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: full', $Station, null, null, null, null
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: not allowed to dock', $Station, null, null, null, null
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: docking not possible', $Station, null, null, null, null
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: stock less than min amount %s required', $Station, $MinAmount, null, null, null
* do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: free volume less than min amount %s required', $Station, $MinAmount, null, null, null

line.text: 'station is buying less than amount requested'

line.comment: * do if $DebugExclusions
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='Excluding %s due to: locked', $Station, null, null, null, null
* secure lock
